    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive core, anchored by Yordan Alvarez and Junior Caminero. Alvarez is in a prime position to anchor our production against Kyle Freeland, benefiting from a massive +14% park factor and favorable platoon splits. Similarly, Caminero offers substantial upside against Javier Assad, as he capitalizes on a +19% SP skill advantage. Colt Keith also projects as a high-floor play from the leadoff spot; his +10% order bonus and strong dynamic platoon metrics against Taj Bradley make him a critical asset for maximizing our Roto efficiency in runs and batting average.\n\nWe face some tactical uncertainty with Christian Yelich and Pete Crow-Armstrong, both of whom carry elevated risk due to challenging SP matchups\u2014specifically against Garrett Crochet and Drew Rasmussen, respectively. While Yelich\u2019s park factor provides a slight buffer, his negative platoon split against a tough lefty remains a concern. We are monitoring the lineups closely for these two spots; should any surprise benchings occur, we will pivot to bench depth to protect our rate stats. With several starters batting in the lower third of the order, specifically O\u2019Hoppe and Scott II, we are banking on efficiency over volume to navigate these mid-range projections.",
